----------
Pitfall #1
----------
It is somewhat complex to implement as more number of classes are involved in the implementation.
They need to be more unit testing.

----------
Pitfall #2
----------
You have to start factory method design from the beginning. it's is not easy to refactor
existing code into factory method pattern.

----------
Pitfall #3
----------
Sometimes this pattern forces you to subclass to create proper instances.

